   <br>
   <strong>Solution</strong>
   <br>
   (i)
   <br>	
   16x + 8y; 8 is the HCF of 16x and 8y
   <br>
   16x + 8y = <strong>8 (2x + y)</strong>
   <br>
   (ii)	
   <br>
   3k<sup>2</sup> – 9k; 3k is the HCF of 3k<sup>2</sup> and 9k
   <br>
   3k<sup>2</sup> – 9k = <strong>3k (k – 3)</strong>
   <br>
   (iii)	
   <br>
   36mn – 12m<sup>2</sup> ; 12m is the HCF 36mn and 12m<sup>2</sup>
   <br>
   36mn – 12m<sup>2</sup> = <strong>12m (3n - m)</strong>
   <br>
   <br>
   <div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
   <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Common Factors with Larger Expressions</h3>
   </div> 
